    NonCallingBytecode

    public class ARRAYSTORE
extends NonCallingSequentialBytecode
    A bytecode that writes a value into an element of an array. If the reference to the array is nil, the computation stops.

    ..., array reference, index, value -> ...

      • ARRAYSTORE

        public ARRAYSTORE(Type type)
        Constructs a bytecode that writes a value into an element of an array. The index, where the array is modified, is provided at runtime through the stack.
        Parameters:
        type - the type of the elements of the array that is created by this bytecode
